.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-9-10::.
There 4 different types of food: onion, cauliflower, apricot, asparagus
The people use 4 different means of transport: boat, subway, roller, bus
1. the person driving the bus is not to the left of the person eating onion##8
2. the person eating asparagus and the person driving the bus have the same parity positions##9
3. the person driving the subway is somewhere to the right of the person driving the roller##5
4. the person eating apricot is on the left or right of the person driving the subway##3
5. the person eating cauliflower is somewhere between the person driving the subway and the person driving the bus##7
6. the person eating asparagus is on the far right##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |   1    |     2      |   3    |     4      |
| Food        | apricot | onion   | cauliflower | asparagus |
| Transport   | roller   | subway | boat    | bus      |

